title: US and China seek to project power with huge and expensive aircraft carriers
summary: China has launched a £5.4 billion aircraft carrier capable of transporting 60 aircraft, highlighting its significance in enhancing Beijing's global influence. While the ship serves a military purpose, it also symbolizes China's growing naval power and ambitions. This development underscores China's strategic efforts to assert its presence on the international stage.

title: Nationwide recall of alfalfa sprouts linked to ‘unusual strain’ of salmonella after dozens infected across Australia
summary: Health authorities in Australia are warning consumers to avoid certain products sold in supermarkets due to safety concerns. These affected items pose health risks and should not be consumed. Authorities are actively monitoring the situation to ensure public safety.

title: Trump-Orbán meeting: US gives Hungary exemption from sanctions on Russian oil and gas
summary: During a friendly summit at the White House, US President praised Hungarian leader Viktor Orbán for his strict immigration policies. The meeting highlighted their alignment on various issues, particularly regarding border security. This collaboration reflects a growing partnership between the two leaders.

title: Graham ‘Richo’ Richardson, former Labor party powerbroker, dies aged 76
summary: Former NSW senator and factional enforcer has passed away at the age of 76 following a prolonged illness. He was prominent in politics and known for his influential role in the factional landscape. His death marks the end of a significant chapter in New South Wales political history.
